<subSubSection id="34A74C76F88D740B4CB569C9B8814915" pageId="0" pageNumber="339" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="E936BFF6266825AF478526E454AFA327" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E0A2A74E8EF9B7AE0FE9FAA2A7AFFEAF" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">
<emphasis id="DA7831736BDE6A60ED93E273D11864ED" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">Both sexes</emphasis>
: clypeus narrower than LID (Figs 
<figureCitation id="9B64F4E03A5386463B347D32CB13B70F" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="91C2E62D0251072F90E9F330CBDEF20E" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., paratype, male (from Kaohsiung, Luluei Forest Sta., 750 m, Taiwan) A head in anterior view B head and pronotum in dorsal view C whole body in lateral view D left fore and hind wings E left flagellomeres 2 - 4 in medial view F metasomal sternum 6 and subgenital plate in ventral view G genitalia in dorsal view H genitalia in ventral view. Scale bar: 0.25 mm (F-H); 0.5 mm (A, B, E); 1 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580435" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">4A</figureCitation>
); mid and hind femora without small spines set in pits apicodorsally. 
<emphasis id="F0BBFF115EE2F12690C12D7DCD8C6A05" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">Female</emphasis>
: thorax almost black (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BB484F8244846D20E834BF43FB66B930" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3G</figureCitation>
); gena, in dorsal view, slightly thickened, roundly receding posteriorly (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6577F6F39195C9BEDA91AC43879CC0E1" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3B</figureCitation>
); and lateral margin of pronotal dorsum, in dorsal view, concave, not narrowing anteriorly (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="47C98FC72C1D028851D9C7C7572AC528" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3B</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="1D85EB83CF827E890489BF9E05245DEF" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">Male</emphasis>
: thorax dark rufous (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2C599A65B3E14D29B83F06ECF9CAB2CC" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., paratype, male (from Kaohsiung, Luluei Forest Sta., 750 m, Taiwan) A head in anterior view B head and pronotum in dorsal view C whole body in lateral view D left fore and hind wings E left flagellomeres 2 - 4 in medial view F metasomal sternum 6 and subgenital plate in ventral view G genitalia in dorsal view H genitalia in ventral view. Scale bar: 0.25 mm (F-H); 0.5 mm (A, B, E); 1 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580435" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">4I</figureCitation>
); frons, in profile, spherically convex (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="80A29D5AE828469D0A4ABCE8B51538D5" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., paratype, male (from Kaohsiung, Luluei Forest Sta., 750 m, Taiwan) A head in anterior view B head and pronotum in dorsal view C whole body in lateral view D left fore and hind wings E left flagellomeres 2 - 4 in medial view F metasomal sternum 6 and subgenital plate in ventral view G genitalia in dorsal view H genitalia in ventral view. Scale bar: 0.25 mm (F-H); 0.5 mm (A, B, E); 1 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580435" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">4I</figureCitation>
); placoids small, shorter than half of each flagellomere (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="DF39CD788F301B6F707D5BDBF79EF422" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., paratype, male (from Kaohsiung, Luluei Forest Sta., 750 m, Taiwan) A head in anterior view B head and pronotum in dorsal view C whole body in lateral view D left fore and hind wings E left flagellomeres 2 - 4 in medial view F metasomal sternum 6 and subgenital plate in ventral view G genitalia in dorsal view H genitalia in ventral view. Scale bar: 0.25 mm (F-H); 0.5 mm (A, B, E); 1 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580435" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">4E</figureCitation>
); SGP triangular with rounded apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AA9BF8792F608CD555E874E4281610DB" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., paratype, male (from Kaohsiung, Luluei Forest Sta., 750 m, Taiwan) A head in anterior view B head and pronotum in dorsal view C whole body in lateral view D left fore and hind wings E left flagellomeres 2 - 4 in medial view F metasomal sternum 6 and subgenital plate in ventral view G genitalia in dorsal view H genitalia in ventral view. Scale bar: 0.25 mm (F-H); 0.5 mm (A, B, E); 1 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580435" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">4F</figureCitation>
); and inner margin of parapenial lobe finely and irregularly serrate (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FEC56DEDEBAEBDDC504FFD662EAF81F6" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., paratype, male (from Kaohsiung, Luluei Forest Sta., 750 m, Taiwan) A head in anterior view B head and pronotum in dorsal view C whole body in lateral view D left fore and hind wings E left flagellomeres 2 - 4 in medial view F metasomal sternum 6 and subgenital plate in ventral view G genitalia in dorsal view H genitalia in ventral view. Scale bar: 0.25 mm (F-H); 0.5 mm (A, B, E); 1 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580435" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">4G, H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B427BD02CBFCCBB16C6BBB28031F360A" pageId="0" pageNumber="339" type="description">
<paragraph id="CF76AF2B3220A18578692C7355315CD1" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2153200538244AC80527E1D00B042A3F" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">
<emphasis id="7DF92F3AFB7FDCC890199F2CCB657E58" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">
<emphasis id="027F6D4AC8606EECE8EBC2736DF5DB14" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">Holotype</emphasis>
female.
</emphasis>
Length: Body 6.0 mm; forewing 5.9 mm. Body and legs black (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="52541073AF407F156F3B5DFEF5F51C0C" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3D</figureCitation>
). Following dark rufous: palpi, clypeus, labrum, mandible, flagellum beneath, legs, and metasoma. Scape and pedicel beneath light brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="94F8F3234E5A8DE636022D5AAFF775B7" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3A</figureCitation>
). Wings translucent with brownish tint (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="412C19AF7FC9B4E873890B4925C85C72" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3F</figureCitation>
). Pubescence on pronotum posteriorly and mesonotum sericeous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7017C13A2C5176E2E605D7FCDF4D159F" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">
Head 1.4 
<normalizedToken id="30784DB399AFBA92EF3F23A3C2D4AACB" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as broad as long. Vertex, in frontal view, almost transversely straight but slightly raised in ocellar area (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="880E85FEBA2810DAFE32CEE7523DDF95" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3A</figureCitation>
). Frons in lateral view strongly convex, but upper frons and vertex flattened (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8C05036E6E422077B28623C0F5D2CF28" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3G</figureCitation>
), with frontal line very fine from antennal base to anterior ocellus. Antennocular line distinctly inclined from antennal base toward eye (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="41DC6CE19DED8AE4D6D75E6B2AECBBFD" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3B</figureCitation>
). MID 0.61 
<normalizedToken id="38D4F781663E1CC529E754E5FB63C930" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
head width. UID:MID:LID = 8.1:10:7.5. POL:OOL = 1:0.86. Clypeus 2.3 
<normalizedToken id="FD08ADEF3167754E732981FABE19C08F" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as broad as long; apical margin barely and arcuately emarginate. Gena, in profile, thin, 0.2 
<normalizedToken id="0279517A2CB1CAE95165BB81CFD423BD" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
eye width (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AF0601AEBDC32D53B58F56018C4CD710" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3G</figureCitation>
). Scape:Fl1:Fl2 = 7.2:10:8.7; Fl1 4.2 
<normalizedToken id="62D1341DAE4833ABB0CB112F1B1FDC30" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as thick, 0.78 
<normalizedToken id="CA907226D0B48C3279EB86653474E2F4" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as UID.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2042EC05324406BD70C9DB2645C8D0F8" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">
Pronotum gently and arcuately emarginate posteriorly (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0E5F0DD54596388F62EC1A5844B2C7DF" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3B</figureCitation>
). Mesoscutum scarcely raised posterolaterally. Disc of scutellum not convex above level of mesoscutum. Metapostnotum 0.1 
<normalizedToken id="E8F27229AF9BE9D53C3A12E049BD529A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as metanotum and depressed medially, with a few fine transverse striae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B7477B8ACD4072594FA77EF66EC68F50" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2FCCE890D9E91AA5B759682590654629" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">
Mid tibia with four spines externally and one spine internally; hind tibia with five or six spines externally and five spines internally (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="07EC15C14259CD99085050D05DEB996A" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3H</figureCitation>
). Longer spur of hind tibia 0.63 
<normalizedToken id="ECDFF63064EB4A614A054AE94B17BAD5" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
hind tarsomere 1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="588D6645FA55980ABA712464B75E84BA" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">
FW and HW as shown in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="36E41B7DED1BAC139B205A1658D6DBBC" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., holotype, female A head in anterior view B head, pronotum, and scutum in dorsal view C scutellum, metanotum, metapostnotum and propodeum in dorsal view D whole body in lateral view E left fore tarsus in dorsal view F left fore and hind wings G head and mesosoma in lateral view H right hind tibia in dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580434" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">3F</figureCitation>
. Marginal cell removed from wing tip by 0.46 
<normalizedToken id="A7D67CA148DC12223456A2812DF45092" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
its own length. SMC2:SMC3 = 1:1.3 on vein 
<emphasis id="17075D0182832A6BB08418BF454D69A7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">M</emphasis>
, 1:0.48 on vein 
<emphasis id="9C5D1DDA0D120200248A15AB84BCFEB2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">Rs.</emphasis>
SMC2 narrowed on vein 
<emphasis id="B3F424631E90D590993018E441B25541" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">Rs</emphasis>
by 0.82 
<normalizedToken id="552A4B93FEAA7F3E0EAF5F7467064FBD" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
its length on vein 
<emphasis id="99DFF69427DE4D54210311CFEDD352F3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">M</emphasis>
, receiving crossvein 
<emphasis id="98303094D82138E4D7DC6F29D7E0CBEA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">1m-cu</emphasis>
at basal 0.5. SMC3 narrowed on vein 
<emphasis id="E33AD7DA66876BF5C141FDBF893A9906" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">Rs</emphasis>
by 0.3 
<normalizedToken id="D0DF657186FF579A43AE36441AA4A611" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
its length on vein 
<emphasis id="F410913B512E4E9A22FDE966540383D1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">M</emphasis>
, receiving crossvein 
<emphasis id="27903CA622FDB0160BCB9C13B64F4566" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">2m-cu</emphasis>
at basal 0.54, removed from outer wing margin by 1.8 
<normalizedToken id="3F10D237E86ABCDA0CFF3E650E8BC892" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
its own length. Crossvein 
<emphasis id="35565D7A8177897F17331F1A9A0A9792" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">cu-a</emphasis>
originating slightly distal to point of separation of vein 
<emphasis id="476EE2A01ACC03B6C8E552EA047A21ED" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">M+CuA</emphasis>
, leaning toward wing base. HW jugal lobe less than third of subbasal cell in length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="18AF55EF0BBC426D0B3EC9D87B90DEB7" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">
<emphasis id="84F83677FC0B2C4A75C452CF426A6DAC" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">Male.</emphasis>
Based on the only paratype. Body 3.8 mm; forewing 3.6 mm. Body and legs reddish brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="63D345B57F9DA65E01BB48EF91B3AD22" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., paratype, male (from Kaohsiung, Luluei Forest Sta., 750 m, Taiwan) A head in anterior view B head and pronotum in dorsal view C whole body in lateral view D left fore and hind wings E left flagellomeres 2 - 4 in medial view F metasomal sternum 6 and subgenital plate in ventral view G genitalia in dorsal view H genitalia in ventral view. Scale bar: 0.25 mm (F-H); 0.5 mm (A, B, E); 1 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580435" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">4C</figureCitation>
); scape and pedicel yellowish brown beneath.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5B2DDBD141767F7CBC248D6F1BCDDC23" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">
Head 1.3 
<normalizedToken id="C1AE1CA1FD59402CD22A623C1B2E678F" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as broad as long. Vertex distinctly convex between eye tops (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="952AEB6E1D349626D5C6A95D7FE67A55" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., paratype, male (from Kaohsiung, Luluei Forest Sta., 750 m, Taiwan) A head in anterior view B head and pronotum in dorsal view C whole body in lateral view D left fore and hind wings E left flagellomeres 2 - 4 in medial view F metasomal sternum 6 and subgenital plate in ventral view G genitalia in dorsal view H genitalia in ventral view. Scale bar: 0.25 mm (F-H); 0.5 mm (A, B, E); 1 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580435" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">4A</figureCitation>
). Antennocular line strongly inclined from antennal base toward eye (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E93B39AA92C39A1E2B24F502CA7414DE" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., paratype, male (from Kaohsiung, Luluei Forest Sta., 750 m, Taiwan) A head in anterior view B head and pronotum in dorsal view C whole body in lateral view D left fore and hind wings E left flagellomeres 2 - 4 in medial view F metasomal sternum 6 and subgenital plate in ventral view G genitalia in dorsal view H genitalia in ventral view. Scale bar: 0.25 mm (F-H); 0.5 mm (A, B, E); 1 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580435" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">4B</figureCitation>
). MID 0.67 
<normalizedToken id="DFF69F139E7205F3CB1EAFBFB5F28F5E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
head width. UID:MID:LID = 8.6:10:7.3. POL:OOL = 1:0.87. Clypeus much narrower than LID (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="160D734CEF6028D3FF5FCB02C4AB31A3" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., paratype, male (from Kaohsiung, Luluei Forest Sta., 750 m, Taiwan) A head in anterior view B head and pronotum in dorsal view C whole body in lateral view D left fore and hind wings E left flagellomeres 2 - 4 in medial view F metasomal sternum 6 and subgenital plate in ventral view G genitalia in dorsal view H genitalia in ventral view. Scale bar: 0.25 mm (F-H); 0.5 mm (A, B, E); 1 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580435" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">4A</figureCitation>
), 2.3 
<normalizedToken id="AFF9401DAF4707834494F6CF310FA621" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as broad as long; surface more convex than in female; apical margin transversely straight. Gena, in profile, 0.3 
<normalizedToken id="A80A8AD58AB9477CCD99F29278F8A145" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
eye width. Scape:Fl1:Fl2 = 8.4:10:10; Fl1 2.4 
<normalizedToken id="3AF8A378EB891B7F66EFD3646A6DBF8C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as thick, 0.54 
<normalizedToken id="075A7505B4F4844786015F3457B50EE1" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as UID.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1EE9344A1E27EA382E82BD8A9FEE9479" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">
Metapostnotum very short, 0.06 
<normalizedToken id="6F6398BAEE4AEB575EA40658F695072F" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as metanotum at midline.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC9ECB2351C6C1B18CB07C1B7D4F2C43" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">
FW and HW as shown in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="17177DB2A0111D3B812598C96C9B1000" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., paratype, male (from Kaohsiung, Luluei Forest Sta., 750 m, Taiwan) A head in anterior view B head and pronotum in dorsal view C whole body in lateral view D left fore and hind wings E left flagellomeres 2 - 4 in medial view F metasomal sternum 6 and subgenital plate in ventral view G genitalia in dorsal view H genitalia in ventral view. Scale bar: 0.25 mm (F-H); 0.5 mm (A, B, E); 1 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580435" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">4D</figureCitation>
. Marginal cell removed from wing tip by 0.38 
<normalizedToken id="E3FAE4B9DBE083D96FE43B33BBF98E06" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
its own length. SMC2:SMC3 = 1:2 on vein 
<emphasis id="AA2A597B3787EAEA2D1EA3FCC18F1647" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">M</emphasis>
, 1:0.67 on vein 
<emphasis id="4D4C25930E18C35B97F92602092ABBBC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">Rs.</emphasis>
SMC2 not narrowed above, receiving crossvein 
<emphasis id="D329E0A8C7A665D46B35D6117C383F74" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">1m-cu</emphasis>
at basal 0.43. SMC3 narrowed on vein 
<emphasis id="9B6051C81A1DB90AC2230E788795165C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">Rs</emphasis>
by 0.34 
<normalizedToken id="0B09432F5EE1FA56C18413359D78C8D6" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
its length on vein 
<emphasis id="BDCD96E7242321E17264E624E5B71907" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">M</emphasis>
, receiving crossvein 
<emphasis id="2C32485102A42798FB8B87BAD089198D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">2m-cu</emphasis>
at basal 0.51, removed from outer wing margin by 1.5 
<normalizedToken id="2E476FC5ACBA155C9914B8114C193DE5" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
its own length. Crossvein 
<emphasis id="4423BC7970D10B2DFD8B56E6059EE154" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">cu-a</emphasis>
perpendicular to vein 
<emphasis id="D07A33D765572DF6AEB134A8B248F0E8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">A</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="66CF38CC6ED3E1B44B64BBB6E01FBE4B" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">
Mid tibia with very small spines dorsally, three spines externally and two spines internally. Hind tibia with spines longer than those on mid tibia, five or six spines externally and three or four spines internally. Longer spur of hind tibia 0.65 
<normalizedToken id="0CF37D3AFE486745AE9B78323F0CE674" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
hind tarsomere 1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="62A64BB408CF82A0E2E29E44A5FA984F" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">
SGP somewhat concave beneath. Genitalia (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7D5407A241DA8A3135BA66BB3476C7EA" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Erythropompilus taiwanensis Pitts &amp; Shimizu, sp. nov., paratype, male (from Kaohsiung, Luluei Forest Sta., 750 m, Taiwan) A head in anterior view B head and pronotum in dorsal view C whole body in lateral view D left fore and hind wings E left flagellomeres 2 - 4 in medial view F metasomal sternum 6 and subgenital plate in ventral view G genitalia in dorsal view H genitalia in ventral view. Scale bar: 0.25 mm (F-H); 0.5 mm (A, B, E); 1 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.84.68810.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/580435" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">4G, H</figureCitation>
): volsella slender but broadened apically with rounded apex and several long setae; parapenial lobe extending far beyond apex of volsella; aedoeagus parallel-sided for most part.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="26D34875D27C9FA993B6BD46D07702A8" pageId="0" pageNumber="339" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="50F97F3634108998C875FC30F14FC386" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="53D84DEF5DD449EA2EE94D72037DA9FF" pageId="0" pageNumber="339">The species name is derived from its locality, i.e., Taiwan.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
